<br>
Sorry guys, but I bet there's alot involved with the whole raid experience thing.<br>
<br>
First concern has to be mass power leveling. I'm still wondering how they dealt with that issue. <br>
<br>
Second concern is amount of exp to give per raider. How to make it fair, yet more appealing to group as 6 people.<br>
<br>
Third is to make chat filters so all the people can communicate with one another.<br>
<br>
Lastly they need to code commands to activate and manipulate it.<br>
<br>
<br>
It's entirely too soon to tell how well this will work, but if it goes the way it looks like then this will be something I would've spent $24.95 a very long time ago to have. No more whinning because groups aren't getting any exp. Think how this helps raid leaders and guild leaders alike...<br>
<br>
I'll be glad when the day comes when last I hear , &quot;Go easy on the next few. Let the others get some experience.&quot;  or the inverse, &quot;Woot! we finally got one!&quot;<br>
<br>
To me a raid is essentially a small army. If within your ranks you have 4 platoons each kill stealing eachother to get experience its not the same as a cohesive unit. <br>
<br>
